fields.description:
I created a pre-sign url http://10.111.5.6:8773/services/objectstorage/import/manifest.xml?Expires=1392838193&AWSAccessKeyId=AKIXBNGYVGV2LVBBD33B&Signature=mUW9AcQP5IFO5ZW5/OBeWuPtXq8%3D

That about every other time return actual object. But in many cases it does return and error that entity does not exist.

com.eucalyptus.util.EucalyptusCloudException: The specified entity was not found Caused by: AmazonS3Exception: Status Code: 404, AWS Service: Amazon S3, AWS Request ID: ecf59586-b0e3-454c-8ebc-806fec4a482f, AWS Error Code: NoSuchEntity, AWS Error Message: The specified entity was not found, S3 Extended Request ID: null com.eucalyptus.util.EucalyptusCloudException: The specified entity was not found at com.eucalyptus.objectstorage.providers.s3.S3ProviderClient.getObjectExtended(S3ProviderClient.java:722) at com.eucalyptus.objectstorage.ObjectStorageGateway.getObjectExtended(ObjectStorageGateway.java:1200) at sun.reflect.NativeMethodAccessorImpl.invoke0(Native Method) at sun.reflect.NativeMethodAccessorImpl.invoke(NativeMethodAccessorImpl.java:57) at sun.reflect.DelegatingMethodAccessorImpl.invoke(DelegatingMethodAccessorImpl.java:43) at java.lang.reflect.Method.invoke(Method.java:606) at org.mule.model.resolvers.AbstractEntryPointResolver.invokeMethod(AbstractEntryPointResolver.java:151) at org.mule.model.resolvers.ReflectionEntryPointResolver.invoke(ReflectionEntryPointResolver.java:121) at org.mule.model.resolvers.DefaultEntryPointResolverSet.invoke(DefaultEntryPointResolverSet.java:39) at org.mule.component.DefaultComponentLifecycleAdapter.invoke(DefaultComponentLifecycleAdapter.java:343) at org.mule.component.AbstractJavaComponent.invokeComponentInstance(AbstractJavaComponent.java:86) at

comments.body: I've created a new url http://10.111.5.6:8773/services/objectstorage/import/manifest.xml?Expires=1392877981&AWSAccessKeyId=AKIXBNGYVGV2LVBBD33B&Signature=hkrVAf6%2B4JFBCCBroeMU8E4xksE%3D that has the same issues.

I am unable to reproduce it against the latest testing  (commit 867ce09eb20d460c43e2735586620bcccf4fb4c8)

This is the object I uploaded.

[neil@ambienwalrus0 ~]$ md5sum upload
